Do NOT reapply 'growth serum' to an already 'grown' item, as it results in negative values. The 'mutation catalyst' consistently produced negative values, so avoid it unless you are experimenting with no risk to your score. message: Hello! My main discovery is that the 'growth serum' is very effective. Always apply 'growth serum' to your initial 0-value ingredients first. It adds +5 to small, +10 to medium, and +15 to large items. Once you have several 'grown' items, combine two of them. Combining two 'grown' items, especially of the same size or bringing together different 'lives in' environments (land+water, land+air), usually increases value significantly. However, be extremely cautious about combining more than two items, or combining items with very different sizes, as this led to massive value decreases for me. Also, avoid using 'growth serum' on items that are already 'grown' or on combined 'grown' items, as this also reduced value. The 'mutation catalyst' seemed to create negative value items, so I recommend avoiding it.

The Mutation Catalyst (ğŸ§¬) is risky: it often makes basic items 'mutant' and negative, but can transform an *already mutant* item into a valuable 'super-mutant'. Avoid using Mutation Catalyst on complex, multi-component hybrids, as it frequently leads to 'corrupted' or 'overcomplicated' negative values. Combining 'grown' items with different 'lives in' features (e.g., land + water for 'amphibious') reliably increases value. However, don't combine too many components or over-modify high-value items (30-40 range) as they might be near their cap and further actions can turn them 'overcomplicated' with severely negative values, resetting your score to 0.
